example_quotes: Medical Student: OK are you, did you have a loss of consciousness when you fell off your bike?
Patient: No, I got right back up. I just just had the pain.

Patient: I actually was riding my bicycle and just fell off on, kind of just slipped and I think I fell on that side like when I the impact was right on my chest and since then it's been really painful.
Medical Student: OK, so any injuries to the head?
Medical Student: Alright, and I know you mentioned the few scratches on your hands, but any other injuries?
Patient: Oh no, I think I got a pretty lucky.
Patient: If I try to take a deep breath it just really hurts like taking those small, smaller breaths helps.
Patient: I feel like I can't catch my breath.
Medical Student: OK, and do you feel the pain anywhere else, or is it just on the left side of your chest?
Patient: No, I would say just on the left side.
Patient: So I came to the emergency Department because I've been having pain in my chest.
Medical Student: OK, where is the pain located?
Patient: I would say it's like the whole pretty much the left side of my chest.
Patient: I feel like I can't catch my breath.
Medical Student: OK are you, did you have a loss of consciousness when you fell off your bike?
Patient: No, I got right back up. I just just had the pain.
Patient: I'd say over the last two hours it's been getting worse.
Patient: I would say like in the last hour a little bit more so than usual.
